body: Sorry there isn't any. All we have is public, in this repo.

Hi @snnn,

Thanks for your reply.

May I know how the Conv kernel(MLAS) is being called on CPU? When I inspect on i7-9th gen the ConvnchwcFMA3 and ConvnchwFMA3 kernels are being called. But I want to understand how there is a link between CPP code to Assembly code.
For example: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/d2b14249683d3e25994c2209027dbf5df9d98c16/onnxruntime/core/mlas/lib/snchwc.cpp#L724 here the Conv kernel is called, but how this call is linked to Assembly code?

Looking forward to your reply.

Thanks,
Darshan

@Darshcg , the assembly code are mainly dynamically bound/linked by the [MLAS_PLATFORM](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/df16c605e8aa287c7936e5fe80fdc337e744804b/onnxruntime/core/mlas/lib/platform.cpp#L105). 

For the Conv kernel case, Kernel is assigned here: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/df16c605e8aa287c7936e5fe80fdc337e744804b/onnxruntime/core/mlas/lib/snchwc.cpp#L678, and the real kernel(assembly) code is linked according to the cpu info (arch, extensions)

Thanks a lot, @yufenglee. 

I inspected the Assembly files for the Conv op being executed on my CPU. And the corresponding files are: 
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/df16c605e8aa287c7936e5fe80fdc337e744804b/onnxruntime/core/mlas/lib/x86_64/SconvKernelFma3.S and https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/df16c605e8aa287c7936e5fe80fdc337e744804b/onnxruntime/core/mlas/lib/x86_64/SconvKernelCommon.h. Can you please assist me in understanding the execution flow of the macros in these two files? and which is the first macro that is being executed in these two files?

Looking forward to your reply

Thanks
Darshan

The first macros are at the end of the file:
https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/df16c605e8aa287c7936e5fe80fdc337e744804b/onnxruntime/core/mlas/lib/x86_64/SconvKernelFma3.S#L242

Thanks a lot for your kind response @yufenglee.

Now I got the flow of the execution of the macros.

Lastly, can you please explain within a few lines about the ProcessFilterCountN, ProcessOutputCountN and computeBlock macros shortly? Would be a great help from your side.

Thanks

Hi @yufenglee,

Looking forward to your reply.

Thanks
